{
  "texts": [
    "In a human study with about 400 participants, Kim et al. (2024) provide evidence that an LLM expressing uncertainty in natural language reduces the users' trust in the system.",
    "Very recently, Yadkori et al. (2024) proposed an information-theoretic metric to distinguish between epistemic and aleatoric uncertainty.",
    "They enable the identification of unreliable model outputs and hallucinations without altering the training process.",
    "It does not fall within the scope of this paper to analyze output uncertainty.",
    "Because LLMs can also behave pseudo-deterministically (Yang et al., 2024a), this limits the impact of some probabilitybased uncertainty quantification metrics."
  ]
}